review_comments_text:
[Review by copilot-pull-request-reviewer[bot]]: ## Pull request overview

Fixes BYOK subagent failures when the user has no GitHub session by short-circuiting the subagent endpoint resolution to reuse the main (BYOK) endpoint whenever it owns its own authorization, avoiding routes that require a Copilot token (agentic proxy / override model).

**Changes:**
- In `ExecutionSubagentToolCallingLoop.getEndpoint` and `SearchSubagentToolCallingLoop.getEndpoint`, resolve the main endpoint up front and return it immediately if `ownsAuthorization` is true.
- Replace the redundant `getChatEndpoint` fallback calls with the cached `mainEndpoint`.
- Add unit tests covering BYOK short-circuit and the existing proxy / override-model / fallback paths.

<details open>
<summary>Show a summary per file</summary>

| File | Description |
| ---- | ----------- |
| extensions/copilot/src/extension/prompt/node/executionSubagentToolCallingLoop.ts | Short-circuit BYOK to main endpoint; reuse resolved `mainEndpoint` in fallback branches. |
| extensions/copilot/src/extension/prompt/node/searchSubagentToolCallingLoop.ts | Same BYOK short-circuit and `mainEndpoint` reuse for the search subagent. |
| extensions/copilot/src/extension/prompt/node/test/executionSubagentToolCallingLoop.spec.ts | New tests covering BYOK, proxy, override model, pwsh fallback, and default paths. |
| extensions/copilot/src/extension/prompt/node/test/searchSubagentToolCallingLoop.spec.ts | New tests covering BYOK and existing routing paths for the search subagent. |
</details>

## Copilot's findings





- **Files reviewed:** 4/4 changed files
- **Comments generated:** 0 | [Inline on extensions/copilot/src/extension/prompt/node/executionSubagentToolCallingLoop.ts L118]: Rather than check for `ownsAuthorization` as a condition to fall back to main agent endpoint, can we just add a try-catch block around the proxy endpoint instantiation? Like this:
```ts
			// Use agentic proxy with ExecutionSubagentModel or default to DEFAULT_AGENTIC_PROXY_MODEL
			const agenticProxyModel = modelName || ExecutionSubagentToolCallingLoop.DEFAULT_AGENTIC_PROXY_MODEL;
			try {
				const endpoint = this.instantiationService.createInstance(ProxyAgenticEndpoint, agenticProxyModel);
			} catch (error) {
				// If the specified model isn't available, fall back to main agent endpoint
				return await this.endpointProvider.getChatEndpoint(this.options.request);
			}
```
This would make it robust to all kinds of errors while instantiating the proxy endpoint.
